textAfterTable: Marygrove Team Statistics Cornerstone 13 (5) Shots (on goal) 8 (1) 1 Saves 3 13 Fouls 17 2 Corner Kicks 7 1 Offsides 4 full stats GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. -- The men's soccer team avenged their season-ending loss a year ago with a 2-0 victory Saturday evening (Oct. 12) on the road at Cornerstone University. The win lifts the Mustangs to 9-4 overall and 4-2 in the WHAC, good for sole possession of third place as Cornerstone drops to 7-5-1 overall and 3-3-1 in the WHAC. Jad El-Zein (Tyre, Lebanon/Dearborn Fordson) got the scoring going early with a free kick that curved around the Golden Eagle wall to beat the keeper. The bender was tallied at the 16:12 mark of the first half as El-Zein converted after a Cornerstone foul was called at the 18-yard marker. The Mustangs – behind strong defensive play from Ahmed Almosawi (Dearborn, Mich./American Muslim Academy), Ali El-Habhab (Saida, Lebanon/Dearborn), Abdoulie Jallow (Bansang, The Gambia/Rust), and Chad Lane (St. Clair Shores, Mich./Lakeview) – set their anchor down by allowing one Cornerstone shot on goal in the first half to take a 1-0 lead into the break.
